From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] p2: co-locate type initialization successful path

Keeping all of pylifecycle.c in the type-init overlay also moves unrelated
lifecycle code into a large group and does not cover the helper calls that
actually evict the static-type loop.  Restore pylifecycle.c to startup group
4 and place the measured 67-function successful-path closure in group 7.
Keep the GIL-build deferred-refcount no-op resident so it never forces a
large overlay load and costs no more than its former stub.

Annotate only the concrete definitions and matching declarations, including
the static forward declarations.  This keeps unrelated functions in their
existing source-assigned overlay groups and leaves non-P2 builds unchanged.
---
